          {
            "type": "rich_text_section",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "I like their approach to conflict resolution and that they explicitly state some commands can lead to non-determinism.  I actually think that for many game types determinism is overrated and their suggestion that you can exploit this as a feature (random selection of a move) is pretty cool.\n\nFacebook Horizon runs actions in order of execution (last action to change state will be the final state) but choosing a random command for immediate actions might have been a cool feature.  I also thought about introducing priority to actions"
